Spanish FM suffers heart attack 
Spanish Foreign Minister Abel Matutes suffered a heart attack Saturday
while he was in hospital having treatment for angina, medical sources
said.
Alberto Torres, head of the clinic where Matutes was in intensive care,
told national radio that the minister suffered a mild heart attack but
was recovering.
Matutes, 55, was on holiday in his home town of Ibiza when he was taken
to hospital overnight with chest pains.
Standing in for him while he is in hospital will be Ramon de Miguel,
the secretary of state for foreign policy and the European Union, and
Fernando Villalonga, secretary of state for cooperation and Latin
America.
